article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 92, UC Irvine 84
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. -- Omondi Amoke had career highs of 23 points and 17 rebounds and D. J. Seeley topped his career best with 27 points Saturday night as Cal State Fullerton beat UC Irvine 92-84. Kwame Vaughn added 25 points for the Titans (12-6, 4-2 Big West). Daman Starring led UC Irvine (6-13, 3-4) with 23 points. Derick Flowers added 18 and Michael Wilder 17. Fullerton dominated the first half, 56-30. The Titans shot 64 percent from the floor while hitting 9 of 14 3-pointers. Irvine, meanwhile, was shooting 39 percent from the field. But Fullerton didn't get a field goal for more than six minutes to open the second half and the Anteaters got hot, making 10 of 16 3-pointers and scoring 54 points after the intermission. Irvine got as close as six points in the waning seconds.
